                <div class="section2Box">
                    <div class="section2BoxTxt">
                        <p>Since 2022, Wahana Visi Indonesia (WVI) has been running <strong> FinWASH4UC</strong>
                            (Financing Water,
                            Sanitation, and Hygiene for Universal Coverage) project.
                        </p>
                        <p>But financing here isn’t just about building pipes. It’s about something more fundamental:
                            <strong> governance.</strong>
                        </p>
                        <p>The project is a co-creation in spirit, meaning it is designed together. First, stakeholders
                            were asked to evaluate the problems themselves. It became clear: water scarcity is about
                            weak commitments, limited funds, lack of understanding, inactive working groups, poor
                            planning platforms, and non-inclusive infrastructure.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="section2BoxTxt"><strong>Toolkit</strong><br>
                        <p>Toolkits were introduced. Local governments and working groups co-designed 5 practical
                            toolkits to identify water and sanitation budgets. Those five are rainwater harvesting
                            tanks,
                            gravity-fed systems, toilets & septic tanks, borehole systems, handwashing facilities</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
